This paper deals with nonmonotonic reasoning and belief revision, which are topics commonly studied in the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also discusses the problem of default entailment, which is related to logic and reasoning (cs.LO). The paper uses a revision process proposed by Nayak, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to the subfield of cryptography (cs.CR) as it discusses the process of iterated revision by sets of sentences. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) as it deals with the process of closure.
